Documentation for the A C Nielsen Household Purchase History Files (HP files)
*****************************************************************************

	The HP files are SAS versions of the A C Nielsen Household Purchase
History files.  The following is a description of the variables contained in
these files.  HP1.SSD (or HP2.SSD) refers to the Nielsen market number one
(or two).


  Variable	Type	Length			Description
  ********	****	******		***************************

1. Major	num	  3 		Indicator for major advertisment

2. Line		num	  3		Indicator for line advertisment

3. Advert	num	  3		Indicator for in-store advertisment

4. Display	num	  3		Indicator for in-store display

5. Cellid	num	  3		Cell Identifier

6. Market	num	  3		ERIM market

7. Trip		num	  3		Trip number for specific ERIM day

8. Id		num	  4		Household identification number

9. Upc		num	  6		Upc number

10. Sid		num	  3		Store identification number

11. Stype	num	  3		Store type (1=grocery, 2=drug)

12. Units	num	  4		Total units purchased

13. Price	num	  4		Price per item, before coupons

14. Weight	num	  4		Unit weight (primary volume)

15. Scc		num	  3		Special coupon code, used to track
					test coupons

16. Scunits	num	  3		Total units purchased on store coupons

17. Scval	num	  4		Total value of store coupons

18. Mcunits	num	  3		Total units purchased on manufacturer
					coupons

19. Mcval	num	  4		Total value of manufacturer coupons

20. Eqv		num	  6		Equivalency factor for converting
					to secondary volume

21. Endd	char	  1		End aisle display code ( Y or N )

22. Frontd	char	  1		Front aisle display code ( Y or N )

23. Ind		char	  1		In-aisle diplay code ( Y or N )

24. Otherd	char 	  1		Other display code ( Y or N )

25. Adcode	char	  1		Advertising code ( Y or N )

26. Adtype	char	  1		Ad type (L=line, M=major, blank=none)

27. Inadcc	char	  1		In-ad coupon code ( Y or N )

28. Pop		char 	  1		Point-of-purchase code ( Y or N )

29. Spc		char	  1		Special price code ( Y or N)

30. Coupfac	char	  1		Coupon factor
					(1=single, 2=double, 3=triple)

31. Date	num	  6		Date in SAS format ( i.e. number of
					days since January 1, 1960)

32. Chain	num	  4		Store chain number

33. Vol 	num	  8		Volume (=units*weight*eqv)
		 
